@startuml seq_11_edit_post
title Sequence Diagram: UC-11 Edit Post

actor User
participant "User Web" as Frontend
participant "Post Controller" as Controller
participant "Post Service" as Service
participant "Post Repo" as PostRepo
participant "Cloudinary" as Cloudinary

User -> Frontend: (1.1) Open existing post for editing
Frontend -> Controller: (1.2) GET /api/posts/{id}
Controller -> Service: (2.1) Load post data
Service -> PostRepo: (2.2) Find post by ID
PostRepo --> Service: (2.3) Post data
Service -> PostRepo: (3.1) Verify ownership
PostRepo --> Service: (3.2) Ownership confirmed
Service --> Controller: (4.1) Editable post content
Controller --> Frontend: (4.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (4.3) Display edit form

User -> Frontend: (6.1) Update title and content
User -> Frontend: (7.1) Mark media changes if needed
User -> Frontend: (8.1) Save changes
Frontend -> Controller: (8.2) PUT /api/posts/{id} (multipart form)
Controller -> Service: (9.1) Update post request

alt Old media marked for removal
    Service -> Cloudinary: (10.1) Delete removed media by public ID
    Cloudinary --> Service: (10.2) Deletion confirmed
    Service -> PostRepo: (11.1) Persist media removal result
end

alt New media attached
    Service -> Cloudinary: (12.1) Upload new media stream
    Cloudinary --> Service: (12.2) Return media URLs and IDs
    Service -> PostRepo: (13.1) Attach new media to post
end

Service -> PostRepo: (9.2) Update post record in DB
PostRepo --> Service: (9.3) Post updated
Service --> Controller: (14.1) Updated post data
Controller --> Frontend: (14.2) 200 OK
Frontend --> User: (14.3) Show updated post
@enduml
